The paper deals with speech recognition, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) in computer science. This suggests that the paper could fall under several sub-categories, including cs.SD (sound), cs.CL (computation and language), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). However, since the paper deals with speech recognition and audio data, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category.
